en_741086_1	The Media Unit also requests the Media Organizations who reported the incident irresponsibly to refrain from such bad journalism.
en_741086_2	Some media outlets brought a news item that a family at the Galenbindunu weva area in Anuradhapura has consumed moringa leaves due to their poverty for many days.
en_741086_3	While paying special attention on the incident the President ordered to appoint a special committee to inquire the plight of the said people.
en_741086_4	As per the findings of the committee, the media outlets have given hype to the incident without divulging into the facts.
en_741086_5	According to the investigations done by the committee members the said family is not that poor like eating moringa leaves for few days.
en_741086_6	The committee had also inquired from the district Secretariat, Divisional Secretariat, Agrarian Department and several other organizations.
en_741086_7	It is revealed that the media organizations had exaggerated the situation.
en_741086_8	The committee had also recorded statements from the various officials including Grama Niladhari,Development Officers and Agricultural officers.
